documentation for how to create a database:
	https://sqlite.org/cli.html

from the command line. use cli 'sqlite3' to create 
	database 'example_db' with tabe 'test' and some entries:
		>sqlite3 example_db
		>sqlite> create table test(name varchar(20), age smallint);
		>sqlite> insert into test values('Alex',50);
		>sqlite> insert into test values('Sasha',30);

download JDBC driver to use the database from a Java program:
	https://bitbucket.org/xerial/sqlite-jdbc/downloads/
include this jar-file driver into project's build path